6c:["$","p","98",{"className":"text-gray-700 leading-relaxed my-4","children":"**$129 — eufy SpaceView Pro**\n- Closed-system (maximum privacy)\n- Excellent night vision\n- Portable parent unit\n- No recurring fees"}]
6d:["$","p","99",{"className":"text-gray-700 leading-relaxed my-4","children":"**$179 — Babysense See** (vs. +$50)\n- Adds: WiFi, app, pan/tilt/zoom\n- Trade-off: Privacy (cloud-based)\n- Value: Depends on whether you want remote access"}]
6e:["$","p","100",{"className":"text-gray-700 leading-relaxed my-4","children":"**$249 — Motorola Halo+** (vs. +$120)\n- Adds: Pan/tilt/zoom, cry detection, breathing detection, premium app\n- Trade-off: Privacy, WiFi dependency, $10/month optional subscription\n- Value: Justified for working parents who want advanced alerts"}]
6f:["$","p","101",{"className":"text-gray-700 leading-relaxed my-4","children":"**$299 — Nanit Pro** (vs. +$170)\n- Adds: Sleep tracking, premium AI, wall-mount design\n- Trade-off: No breathing detection, privacy concerns, $10/month subscription\n- Value: Justified for parents interested in sleep data"}]
70:["$","p","102",{"className":"text-gray-700 leading-relaxed my-4","children":"**$399 — Owlet Dream Duo 2** (vs. +$270)\n- Adds: Wearable sock sensor (breathing, heart rate, oxygen), most features\n- Trade-off: Most expensive, wearable sensor to maintain, privacy concerns\n- Value: Justified only for babies with respiratory concerns or anxiety-driven parents"}]
71:["$","h2","103",{"className":"text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4","children":"Recommendation Framework"}]
72:["$","p","104",{"className":"text-gray-700 leading-relaxed my-4","children":"**Budget ($80-130):** Choose based on privacy preference\n- Want maximum privacy: **eufy SpaceView Pro** ($129)\n- Want simplicity: **VTech RM5764** audio monitor ($89)\n- Both excellent; minimal feature difference"}]
73:["$","p","105",{"className":"text-gray-700 leading-relaxed my-4","children":"**Value ($150-200):** Adding WiFi and remote monitoring\n- Want closed-system security: **Infant Optics DXR-8 Pro** ($149)\n- Want WiFi convenience: **Babysense See** ($179) or **Cubo AI Plus** ($199)\n- Verdict: Only upgrade if you actively need remote viewing"}]
74:["$","p","106",{"className":"text-gray-700 leading-relaxed my-4","children":"**Premium ($250-300):** WiFi with advanced alerts\n- Want cry detection: **Motorola Halo+** ($249) — Best value premium monitor\n- Want sleep tracking: **Nanit Pro** ($299)\n- Verdict: Only if you work away from home and want app-based alerts"}]
75:["$","p","107",{"className":"text-gray-700 leading-relaxed my-4","children":"**Luxury ($350-400):** Maximum features including wearable\n- **Owlet Dream Duo 2** ($399) — Only for specific needs (respiratory concerns, severe anxiety)\n- Verdict: Most features are \"nice to have\" not \"need to have\""}]
76:["$","h2","108",{"className":"text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4","children":"Cost vs. Peace of Mind"}]
77:["$","p","109",{"className":"text-gray-700 leading-relaxed my-4","children":"The question isn't always \"what's the best monitor\" but \"what will give me peace of mind for my budget?\""}]
78:["$","ul","110",{"className":"list-disc list-inside space-y-2 my-4","children":[["$","li","0",{"className":"text-gray-700","children":"**$89-129:** Proven reliable monitors; most families find these sufficient"}],["$","li","1",{"className":"text-gray-700","children":"**$179-199:** Meaningful WiFi upgrades; justifiable for working parents"}],["$","li","2",{"className":"text-gray-700","children":"**$249-300:** Useful alerts; justified for anxious parents or those needing remote access"}],["$","li","3",{"className":"text-gray-700","children":"**$399+:** Diminishing returns; premium features don't significantly improve safety or sleep quality"}]]}]
79:["$","h2","111",{"className":"text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4","children":"Conclusion"}]
7a:["$","p","112",{"className":"text-gray-700 leading-relaxed my-4","children":"The most useful smart features worth paying for:\n1. **Cry detection** — Provides genuine convenience and peace of mind\n2. **Pan/tilt/zoom** — Covers larger nurseries and active babies\n3. **Two-way audio** — Extremely practical for soothing without entering room\n4. **Temperature monitoring** — Important for safety\n5. **WiFi remote monitoring** — Only if you actually need it (don't pay for features you won't use)"}]
7b:["$","p","113",{"className":"text-gray-700 leading-relaxed my-4","children":"Features to skip or avoid:\n- **Breathing detection** — Psychological rather than medical benefit; not proven for healthy babies\n- **AI sleep tracking** — Nice for data-driven parents but not essential\n- **Lullabies** — Separate sound machine works just as well\n- **Wall mount** — Aesthetic preference, not functional necessity"}]
7c:["$","p","114",{"className":"text-gray-700 leading-relaxed my-4","children":"**Best overall value:** **eufy SpaceView Pro** ($129) or **Motorola Halo+** ($249) depending on whether you need WiFi remote access."}]
7d:["$","p","115",{"className":"text-gray-700 leading-relaxed my-4","children":"**Avoid:** $350+ monitors unless you have specific medical needs; most families find $150-250 monitors provide all necessary features."}]
7e:["$","p","116",{"className":"text-gray-700 leading-relaxed my-4","children":"Remember: The best baby monitor is the one you'll actually use. An affordable monitor that you monitor consistently is more valuable than an expensive \"smart\" monitor that you ignore."}]
